We expect to continue to incur net losses for the foreseeable future as we focus on growing our services in both the United States and internationally. The timing and amount of our operating and capital expenditures will depend on many factors, including:
•the amount of net revenue generated by sales of our Passenger and Medical services;
•our decision to purchase aircraft and/or vehicles;
•our launch of new Medical services, passenger routes and/or products;
•the costs and expenses of expanding our U.S. and international operations;
•the extent to which our urban air mobility services are utilized by fliers in the regions we operate;
•the costs incurred in our efforts to develop our brand and improve awareness;
•the costs, timing and outcomes of any future litigation; and
•the level of our selling, general and administrative expenses.
Because of the numerous risks and uncertainties associated with our expansion and commercialization, we are unable to accurately predict the timing or amount of increased expenses or when, or if, we will be able to achieve or maintain profitability.
